## 3. Bugs and Code Quality Issues

### 🔴 BUG-001: Backpressure Depth Always Zero (Severity: CRITICAL)

**File:** [bus.py:50](file:///c:/Users/sergi/colony/backend/col/engine/coe-kernel/core/event_bus/bus.py#L50)

```python
if not self.backpressure.is_accepting(0):  # ← always 0
```

The backpressure controller is **never fed real queue depth**. The `current_depth` parameter is hardcoded to `0`, which means backpressure will **never activate organically**. The test only works because it manually mutates `deactivation_depth = -1`. In production, backpressure is effectively **dead code**.

> [!CAUTION]
> This means the system has **zero protection against event flooding** in production. A malicious or buggy publisher can exhaust memory with unlimited events.

---

### 🔴 BUG-002: EventStore Silently Accepts Out-of-Order Events (Severity: HIGH)

**File:** [store.py:109-111](file:///c:/Users/sergi/colony/backend/col/engine/coe-kernel/core/event_bus/store.py#L109-L111)

```python
if event.sequence_number <= self._current_sequence:
    # Although EventBus enforces this, the store should be defensive
    pass  # ← silently accepts and writes the duplicate
```

The guard detects out-of-order writes but takes **no action** — the event is still written and [_current_sequence](file:///c:/Users/sergi/colony/backend/col/engine/coe-kernel/core/event_bus/store.py#54-57) is updated anyway (line 122). This violates the "No Hidden Mutation" zero-tolerance rule. The store should either **raise an error** or **skip the write entirely**.

---

### 🟠 BUG-003: No Failed Routing Audit (Severity: MEDIUM)

**File:** [bus.py:115-122](file:///c:/Users/sergi/colony/backend/col/engine/coe-kernel/core/event_bus/bus.py#L115-L122)

Spec §Audit Integration: *"Every successful/failed routing attempt is audited."*

When a subscriber crashes and the event goes to DLQ, **no audit entry is created** for the failed routing. Only the `event_published` action is audited (line 67). The DLQ append at line 122 is not accompanied by an audit entry.

---

### 🟠 BUG-004: Interface Signature Mismatch (Severity: MEDIUM)

**File:** [interfaces.py:79](file:///c:/Users/sergi/colony/backend/col/engine/coe-kernel/core/interfaces.py#L79)

```python
# ABC declares:
def subscribe(self, event_type: str, handler: Any) -> None:

# Implementation has:
def subscribe(self, event_type: str, handler: Any, subscriber_id: str = "") -> None:
```

The `subscriber_id` parameter exists in the implementation but **not in the ABC**. This means the interface contract is incomplete — code relying on the ABC won't know `subscriber_id` exists.

---

### 🟡 BUG-005: `datetime.utcnow()` Deprecation (Severity: LOW)

**File:** [dlq.py:23](file:///c:/Users/sergi/colony/backend/col/engine/coe-kernel/core/event_bus/dlq.py#L23)

`datetime.utcnow()` is deprecated in Python 3.12+. Should use `datetime.now(timezone.utc)` for forward compatibility.

---

## 4. Architectural Gaps (Not Production-Grade)

### GAP-001: No Schema Registry (CRITICAL)

The spec and project plan both list "Schema Registry" as a Phase 2 key deliverable. **It does not exist.** The current validation is a hardcoded `"data" in payload` check — this is not a schema registry. A production Event Bus needs:
- Registered event type schemas (JSON Schema or equivalent)
- Version compatibility checking
- Schema hash validation for tamper detection

### GAP-002: No Signature Validation (CRITICAL)

The [Event](file:///c:/Users/sergi/colony/backend/col/engine/coe-kernel/core/types.py#42-56) dataclass has a `signature` field but it is **never validated**. The spec says `"signature": "sha256"`. No code computes, verifies, or rejects invalid signatures. Any tampered event will be accepted.

### GAP-003: No Subscriber Timeout (HIGH)

Spec §4: *"Each subscriber executes within a try/except/timeout boundary."* The timeout boundary is missing. A subscriber that hangs forever will block the entire synchronous bus indefinitely.

### GAP-004: No `gc.get_objects()` Memory Monitoring (HIGH)

Spec §4: *"Best-effort memory monitoring using object count deltas."* Not implemented. No memory abuse detection exists.

### GAP-005: No `system.backpressure` Event Emission (MEDIUM)

Project plan Test Group 6: *"system.backpressure event emitted."* When backpressure activates, the system raises a [KernelError](file:///c:/Users/sergi/colony/backend/col/engine/coe-kernel/core/errors.py#35-53) but does **not** emit a `system.backpressure` event for observability.

### GAP-006: No Metering Integration (MEDIUM)

Spec §Metering: *"Increments event emission counts and wall-clock execution metrics per module."* The Event Bus does not call the Metering Layer at all. Event counts are not tracked per-module.

### GAP-007: DLQ is Not Persistent (MEDIUM)

The DLQ is in-memory only. On process restart, all dead-lettered events are lost. For a "nervous system" this is unacceptable in production.

### GAP-008: No [__init__.py](file:///c:/Users/sergi/colony/backend/col/engine/coe-kernel/core/__init__.py) Package File (LOW)

**File:** `core/event_bus/` directory

The `core/event_bus/` directory has no [__init__.py](file:///c:/Users/sergi/colony/backend/col/engine/coe-kernel/core/__init__.py). This causes the IDE `Unable to import` errors seen throughout the session.

---

## 5. Zero Tolerance Baseline Assessment

| Rule | Status | Evidence |
|---|---|---|
| **No Silent Drops** | ❌ FAIL | DLQ append has no audit trail (BUG-003). Store silently accepts duplicates (BUG-002) |
| **Deterministic Routing** | ✅ PASS | Subscriber sort by UUID verified |
| **No Hidden Mutation** | ❌ FAIL | Store writes out-of-order events without error (BUG-002) |
| **No Audit Bypass** | ❌ FAIL | Failed routing attempts not audited (BUG-003) |
| **Identical input = Identical routing** | ✅ PASS | Sequential dispatch proven |

